race.description: Big Event Picnic Tables Mdn Plate
race.comment: The local OUR JUSTIFY (11) jumped out well and missed a whisker here on debut. She had to cover ground after settling rearward, and there was a stack of merit in the effort. Will have to go it the hard way again, but she will present fitter and can win with average luck. VEOMAS (8) also draws wide, but he brings two provincial placings to peak and didn't have the best of it at Cranbourne last time. He has more to give and will also be finishing hard. SILVER BULLET (7) resumes and has won both Pakenham jumpouts. He's going to show more than we saw on debut. THANKFUL SMILE (12) resumes for a top metro stable and carries just 53kg with Radley's claim. Maps for the run of the race and on what we've seen at the jumpouts, she can't be taken lightly.
